clock().details: Clock (as specified in EIP-6372) is set to match the token's clock.      Fallback to block numbers if the token does not implement EIP-6372.

returns._0: Current quorum, in terms of number of votes: `supply * quorumNumerator / quorumDenominator`.

params._force: Option to forcibly make a request to delete the output.
params._outputIndex: Index of output to be deleted.

params._l2BlockNumber: The L2 block number to be validated.
params._outputRoot: The L2 output of the checkpoint block to be validated.

returns._0: Semver contract version as a string.

params.outputIndex: Index of output to be deleted.

params.l2BlockNumber: The L2 block number to be validated.
params.outputRoot: The L2 output of the checkpoint block to be validated.

COLOSSEUM().notice: The address of the colosseum contract. Can be updated via upgrade.

GOVERNOR().notice: The address of the governor contract. Can be updated via upgrade.

confirmTransaction(uint256).notice: Allows an owner to confirm a transaction.

executeTransaction(uint256).notice: Allows anyone to execute a confirmed transaction.

getConfirmationCount(uint256).notice: Returns the number of confirmations that account has confirmed.

isConfirmed(uint256).notice: Returns the confirmation status of a transaction.

isConfirmedBy(uint256,address).notice: Returns whether the account has confirmed the transaction.

outputsDeleteRequested(uint256).notice: A mapping of outputs requested to be deleted.

quorum().notice: Returns the current quorum, in terms of number of votes.

requestDeletion(uint256,bool).notice: Requests to delete an output to Colosseum forcefully.         This should only be called by one of the Security Council when undeniable bugs occur.

requestValidation(bytes32,uint256,bytes).notice: Allows the Colosseum to request for validate output data.

revokeConfirmation(uint256).notice: Allows an owner to revoke a transaction.

submitTransaction(address,uint256,bytes).notice: Allows an owner to submit and confirm a transaction.

version().notice: Returns the full semver contract version.

ConfirmationRevoked(address,uint256).notice: Emitted when anyone revoke a confirmation.

DeletionRequested(uint256,uint256).notice: Emitted when an output is requested to be deleted.

TransactionConfirmed(address,uint256).notice: Emitted when anyone confirm a transaction.

TransactionSubmitted(address,uint256).notice: Emitted when anyone submit a transaction.

ValidationRequested(uint256,bytes32,uint.notice: Emitted when a validation request is submitted.

userdoc.notice: SecurityCouncil receives validation requests for specific output data,         and allows security council parties to validate & agree on transactions before execution.
